body:
@TimvdLippe after correction of example ( [example.zip](https://github.com/mockito/mockito/files/592106/example.zip) ) as

``` diff
@@ -5,7 +5,7 @@ public class ExampleTest {
   @Test
   public void test() {
     Example spy = spy(new Example());
-    when(spy.getName()).thenReturn("spy");
+    doReturn("spy").when(spy).getName();
     spy.sayHello();
   }
 }
```

**Mockito 1.9.5**, **1.10.19** and **2.2.16 with default mock maker** as expected:
![normal](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/138671/20308310/922b2816-ab43-11e6-8147-ed07d94e8ba8.png)

**2.2.16 with inline mock maker** still no coverage.

Well, we added a hack to read the original class file instead of the pre-instrumented class file in order to retain parameter name information which is currently erased [due to a bug in the VM](http://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=JDK-8168623). We added an [additional class file resolver](https://github.com/mockito/mockito/blob/release/2.x/src/main/java/org/mockito/internal/creation/bytebuddy/InlineBytecodeGenerator.java#L144) that checks the file system first to supply this retention and to fix #695.

We basically can support parameter names **or** the combination with other agents. We cannot do both.

@mockito/developers, maybe we should add a system property to let a user decide what they need more?
